3. It makes us perfect in our ſpiritual part;

                  Vid. Stuck. Antiq conviv. l. 2. c. 26. 
               The ſpirits of juſt men made perfect, Heb. 12.23. it gives us our white and triumphal robes, Rev. 6.11. 7.14. It fits us to be preſented unto God without ſpot or wrinkle, Epheſ. 5.27. the bodies of the Saints when they were dead were waſhed, Act. 9.37. both as a pledge of the reſurrection, and alſo as an Emblem and teſtimony of that cleanneſs and purity, wherein death did deliver their ſouls up unto God.
